      "about.s03.lede": "Several of our customers asked that their use of the platform remain off the public record. In construction and real estate, the choice of engineering platform can itself carry competitive weight. We respect that.",
      "about.s04.lede": "An independent board is being assembled to provide governance through the platform's growth phase. Composition is being structured around financial discipline, regulatory authority, and operational deployment across the markets the firm serves.",
      "about.s05.lede": "Senior practitioners advising on platform direction, regulatory compliance across jurisdictions, and operational deployment. The first cohort is being formed from active practitioners in each discipline the platform covers.",
      "about.s06.lede": "The portal is operational. Upload a project file, run an analysis, get a deliverable in the format you need. No pilot required to see what the platform actually does.",
      "about.disc.foot": "8 organizations ยท active engineering delivery ยท names private by convention",
      "platform.s02.lede": "The five engineering disciplines that produce signed, professionally attested deliverables. Each module is reviewed and signed by a qualified engineer with regulatory authority before any deliverable leaves the platform.",
      "platform.s03.lede": "Five modules that surround the core disciplines and capture the complementary deliverables consulting engineers produce across a project lifecycle. Engineer-reviewed rather than fully attested. Improve project velocity, extend platform value, and compound margin.",
      "platform.s04.lede": "Five modules operating at full automation โ where the market accepts machine-produced output as a valid decision basis. Lowest unit price, highest margin, infinite scalability. Extend the platform to adjacent buyers without scaling expert capacity.",
      "platform.s05.lede": "Every module above runs on the same architecture. Six foundations support the entire platform. New modules and new jurisdictions plug in without architectural changes โ the foundations carry them.",
      "platform.s06.lede": "Every module above is live in the portal today. Upload a real project, run a real analysis, get a real deliverable. No demo environment, no sandbox โ the platform you read about is the platform you use.",
      "industries.s02.lede": "Some Builtly modules โ particularly the fully automated tier โ are bought directly by the parties consultancies traditionally serve. These customers want the underlying analysis without the consulting markup, and the modules are designed to deliver it under regulatory rigour.",
      "industries.s03.lede": "Specific scenarios where the platform replaces or compresses work that currently takes a consultancy weeks. The pattern is consistent across segments: a decision that needs technical underpinning, a timeline that does not allow for traditional consulting, and a regulatory standard that the output must satisfy regardless.",
      "industries.s04.lede": "Builtly is engaged through three commercial routes depending on the segment, the deal size and the regulatory context. The underlying platform is the same; the wrapping varies.",
      "industries.s05.lede": "Engineering consultancies talk to us about platform licences. End buyers can use the portal directly today. Partners and integrators engage via the contact route โ typical conversations start with a 30-minute call.",
      "careers.s01.lede": "Builtly is run as the kind of company an engineer would want to work in. The principles below are not aspirational โ they govern how decisions get made.",
      "careers.s02.lede": "We hire across the platform and across engineering disciplines. Every role is permanent, with a real ownership stake. If a role describes someone close to you but not exactly you โ apply anyway. We hire for trajectory.",
      "careers.s03.lede": "Four conversations. No technical hazing. No multi-week take-homes. We know your time is expensive, and so is ours. The process is built to give both sides enough signal to decide well โ and nothing more.",
      "careers.s04.lede": "If you are senior, technical, and the principles above describe how you already work โ send a note. We hire ahead of need when the right person appears, and we'd rather meet you early than perfectly on time.",
      "contact.s01.lede": "Each route has a dedicated owner, a typical response time, and a short list of what to include so the conversation can start at the right depth. Pick the closest match โ the wrong inbox simply gets forwarded, but the right one gets a faster answer.",
      "contact.s02.lede": "Builtly is a small team. We do not pretend to staff a 24/7 inbound function. We respond inside the windows below, every business day. Outside these windows the inbox is monitored for urgent items but not actively worked.",
      "contact.s03.lede": "Operational facts about Builtly Engineering โ for procurement, vendor onboarding, legal review, and the kind of routine commercial diligence that needs to happen before a contract gets signed.",
      "contact.s04.lede": "The most useful inquiry is short, specific, and gets to the actual question or request quickly. We do not require any of the items below โ but inquiries that include them tend to get more useful first responses.",
      "contact.s05.lede": "If none of the four routes fit, send to the general inbox below. It is monitored daily and forwarded to the right owner. No category, no triage form โ just a real person reading.",
      "trust.s01.lede": "Trust on a platform that produces regulated engineering deliverables is not a feature โ it is a precondition. Three principles govern every architectural decision below them.",
      "trust.s02.lede": "Engineering project data is among the most sensitive a firm holds โ drawings under non-disclosure, client information under contract, and regulatory submissions where leakage carries real cost. Builtly handles it accordingly.",
      "trust.s03.lede": "Security as a property of the architecture rather than a layer above it. Authentication, authorisation, encryption and isolation are built into the foundations on which the modules run โ not configured after the fact.",
      "trust.s04.lede": "For deliverables that an engineer signs and a client submits to a regulator, the chain of custody matters as much as the result. Every claim in every signed deliverable is traceable to the data and the compute behind it.",
      "trust.s05.lede": "The platform is not the regulated party โ the engineer who signs is. But the platform operates in close proximity to regulated work, and is built to support the compliance obligations that flow from that proximity.",
      "trust.s06.lede": "How the platform is operated, how incidents are handled, and what to expect on availability. Builtly is a production platform serving engineering consultancies โ operational discipline is not optional.",
      "trust.s07.lede": "For procurement, vendor onboarding, security review and contracting, the standardised diligence pack is available on request. Security inquiries route to a dedicated inbox. Critical security disclosures get acknowledged within 24 hours.",
      "about.glance.lede": "Builtly Engineering is an engineering automation platform built for the Nordic and German markets. Below: the operational facts as of public launch โ scope, scale, and architecture.",
