      "about.prin.p1.h": "Built on engineering accountability.",
      "about.prin.p1.body": "Every module is reviewed by professional engineers with regulatory authority across multiple disciplines. The signature on the deliverable is the same person who carries the liability.",
      "about.prin.p2.h": "Run with operating experience.",
      "about.prin.p2.body": "Leadership combines decades of operational experience in real estate development and engineering project delivery โ not pure software backgrounds attempting to retrofit an industry.",
      "about.prin.p3.h": "Engineered as software.",
      "about.prin.p3.body": "Proprietary multi-engine AI architecture, deterministic numerical computation, BIM-native processing โ built to industrial-software standards from day one, not retrofitted on top of consulting workflows.",
      "about.thesis.p1": "The consulting engineering industry is built on professional accountability, regulation and quality assurance โ all correct, all preserved at Builtly. <strong>What is not preserved is the assumption that the only way to ship a signed deliverable is to do every step by hand.</strong>",
      "about.thesis.p2": "What has changed is what's technically possible. AI, geometry processing and distributed compute have matured over the past five years to a level where compliance-grade engineering software can be delivered as one coherent portal โ not patched together from disparate tools. <strong>Builtly is the tool for engineers who want to use that maturity now.</strong>",
      "about.thesis.p3": "Builtly's thesis is that the structure of consulting engineering can be preserved while its production layer is rebuilt as software. Mathematics and physics as deterministic code. Regulatory compliance as machine-readable logic. AI as the connective layer between project data and finished deliverables. Engineering judgment as the signature on the result.",
      "about.thesis.p4": "<strong>The platform is operational. The portal is live. The principles are not negotiable.</strong>",
      "index.algo.c1.num": "01 ยท Geometric",
      "index.algo.c1.h3": "Voronoi tessellation",
      "index.algo.c1.body": "Partitions a plane into regions where each region contains all points closest to a single seed. In structural engineering this derives load tributary areas from column or wall positions.",
      "index.algo.c2.num": "02 ยท Numerical",
      "index.algo.c2.h3": "Finite element method",
      "index.algo.c2.body": "Discretizes continuous structural domains into a mesh of simple elements, then solves the partial differential equations governing stress, strain and displacement under load.",
      "index.algo.c3.num": "03 ยท Optimization",
      "index.algo.c3.h3": "Linear programming",
      "index.algo.c3.body": "Selects optimal profile dimensions from regulatory catalogs by minimizing material cost under load-capacity, deflection and serviceability constraints โ guaranteed feasible solutions.",
      "index.algo.c4.num": "04 ยท Logical",
      "index.algo.c4.h3": "Constraint propagation",
      "index.algo.c4.body": "Maintains consistency across modules as inputs change. When the FEM module updates a beam, dependent modules โ connections, footings, fire ratings โ recompute automatically through the constraint graph.",
      "index.algo.c5.num": "05 ยท Spatial",
      "index.algo.c5.h3": "R-tree spatial indexing",
      "index.algo.c5.body": "O(log n) geometry queries over tens of thousands of building elements. Without it, every \"what intersects this zone\" question would linearly scan the entire model. With it: instant.",
      "index.algo.c6.num": "06 ยท Integration",
      "index.algo.c6.h3": "Gaussian quadrature",
      "index.algo.c6.body": "Computes loads over surfaces and volumes by numerical integration. Required for wind-pressure distribution, snow drift on roof geometry, and area-loaded live loads on irregular shapes.",
      "index.algo.used_l": "Used in",
      "index.algo.used_platform": "Used platform-wide",
      "stats.modules": "Engineering modules<br/>in daily delivery",
      "stats.frameworks": "Regulatory<br/>frameworks",
