      "plt.found.regEngine.h4": "Regulation engine.",
      "plt.found.audit.h4": "Audit and traceability.",
      "plt.tier.attested.p": "Five modules covering the disciplines that legally require professional engineering authority. Highest unit price, signed under regulatory liability, professional indemnity coverage in place.",
      "plt.tier.reviewed.p": "Five modules covering complementary deliverables across the project lifecycle. Engineer-reviewed but typically without professional liability attached. Compounding margin as the platform's draft quality improves.",
      "plt.tier.auto.p": "Five modules covering analyses where the market accepts fully automated output as decision basis. Lowest unit price, highest margin, unlimited scale.",
      "plt.mod.geo.body": "Builtly's geotechnical module ingests soil-survey data, regional geological surveys and topographic information to produce ground-bearing capacity assessments, foundation strategy recommendations and Eurocode 7-compliant calculations.",
      "plt.mod.geo.use": "Used at the early-design stage to set foundation strategy and at the detailed-design stage to verify capacity. Attested by an engineer with regulatory authority.",
      "plt.mod.struct.body": "Reads DWG, DXF and IFC4 inputs, runs a structural rationality analysis across the model, applies Eurocode-1 through Eurocode-9 verification, and produces dimensioning calculations, BIM exports and structured reports.",
      "plt.mod.struct.use": "Used for both feasibility-stage rationality reviews and detailed-design dimensioning. The output is reviewed by a structural engineer and attested under regulatory authority.",
      "plt.mod.fire.body": "Develops the fire-safety concept document for a building from plan inputs, applies jurisdiction-specific code requirements, calculates compartmentation and egress, and produces marked-up plans with the technical fire report.",
      "plt.mod.fire.use": "Used at concept stage and again at detailed design. Attested by a fire engineer with regulatory authority.",
      "plt.mod.acoust.body": "Computes airborne and impact-sound insulation requirements between dwellings and between functional zones, verifies sound-class compliance, calculates room acoustics for performance spaces, and produces the technical acoustic report with calculation appendix.",
      "plt.mod.acoust.use": "Used to verify acoustic design at planning approval and at construction documentation. Attested by an acoustic consultant with regulatory authority.",
      "plt.mod.env.body": "Assesses environmental conditions for a site โ contaminated ground risk, biodiversity exposure, regulatory environmental requirements โ applies jurisdiction-specific environmental code, and produces the environmental plan and monitoring schedule.",
      "plt.mod.env.use": "Used at site-acquisition due diligence, at planning application, and to govern environmental monitoring through construction. Attested by an environmental consultant with regulatory authority.",
      "plt.mod.feas.body": "Combines cadastral data, planning regulations and geospatial inputs to produce a site feasibility study โ buildable area, indicative volumes and zoning constraints.",
      "plt.mod.feas.use": "Used by developers and land owners at the acquisition or early-feasibility stage to assess what a site can support before committing capital.",
      "plt.mod.dd.body": "Produces transaction-grade technical due diligence reports โ building condition, regulatory exposure, capex requirements, environmental concerns and contractor risk โ for property transactions.",
      "plt.mod.dd.use": "Used by investors, developers and asset managers at acquisition, refinancing or major portfolio reviews. Engineer-reviewed before delivery.",
      "plt.mod.tender.body": "Constructs the tender checklist for a project, runs received bids against contract criteria, identifies deviations and produces the technical-procurement evaluation document.",
      "plt.mod.tender.use": "Used by clients running competitive tenders and by contractors responding to large bids. Engineer-reviewed for contract-significant findings.",
      "plt.mod.cost.body": "Extracts quantities directly from IFC4 models, classifies materials and assemblies, generates estimating-basis documents structured for downstream cost-plan and procurement tooling.",
      "plt.mod.cost.use": "Used by estimators, quantity surveyors and procurement teams at design milestones and tender preparation. Engineer-reviewed for cost-significant classifications.",
      "plt.mod.hse.body": "Constructs the project HSE plan, builds the project-specific risk register from typology and site factors, defines mitigation strategies and produces the project execution tracker.",
      "plt.mod.hse.use": "Used by clients, principal contractors and HSE coordinators from project inception through completion. Engineer-reviewed for completeness.",
      "plt.mod.climate.body": "Computes climate risk exposure for an individual asset across flood, landslide, sea-level rise and other regulatory climate-risk dimensions. Outputs a structured report aligned to financial-sector disclosure frameworks.",
      "plt.mod.climate.use": "Used by banks, asset managers, insurers and real-estate platforms for portfolio-level climate-risk assessment. Fully automated, suitable for high-volume runs.",
      "plt.mod.sust.body": "Runs a pre-assessment against the relevant sustainability certification framework โ points achievable, evidence required, project-specific recommendations โ and produces a structured pre-assessment document.",
      "plt.mod.sust.use": "Used by developers, design teams and sustainability consultants at early design to decide whether certification is feasible and what target level is appropriate.",
      "plt.mod.traf.body": "Estimates traffic generation for a project, evaluates capacity against existing road geometry, and produces the traffic-impact contribution to the planning application.",
      "plt.mod.traf.use": "Used by developers and planning consultants preparing planning applications. Fully automated for standard residential and commercial typologies.",
      "plt.mod.credit.body": "Produces the technical-credit basis document for construction lending โ building economics, technical risk, regulatory exposure โ automatically per asset for high-volume credit pipelines.",
      "plt.mod.credit.use": "Used by banks, alternative lenders and developer finance teams across loan origination and through the construction monitoring cycle.",
      "plt.found.regEngine.p1": "The mechanism by which the platform scales across markets. Each country pack contains the jurisdiction-specific regulatory logic, standards and code references that every module operates against.",
      "plt.found.regEngine.p2": "Used internally by every other module; surfaced externally as the regulatory framework selection on each delivery. Operational across seven jurisdictions today.",
      "plt.found.audit.p1": "Every claim in a signed deliverable can be traced back to the source data behind it. SHA-256 signing on each version, complete audit trail per project, machine-readable rule pack version stamped on output.",
